\subsection{YPd${_2}$P${_2}$ and LaPd${_2}$P${_2}$}

YPd${_2}$P${_2}$ and LaPd${_2}$P${_2}$ exhibit magnetic and electronic properties consistent with the empty 4\textit{f}-shells of Y and La ions. The zero-field resistivity ($\rho(T)$) in Fig.\ref{LaYPd2P2}(a) demonstrates characteristic metallic behavior with an almost linear increase of the resistivity with temperature for $T>75$~K, with no observed anomalies down to 1.8~K. The residual resistivity ratios, RRR$\equiv\rho(300\text{K})/\rho(2\text{K})$), of YPd${_2}$P${_2}$ and LaPd${_2}$P${_2}$ are 2.4 and 7.8 respectively. 

